<subSubSection id="51C4019CBD8328C7E5E2E17A2B7CF2E7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="E10B5C06C59A4C99C377194806DD6395" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A2CAE608751C062767B18A74A6ECDC1C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Mexico (Hidalgo, Oaxaca, Puebla, Veracruz) in cloud forest, tropical dry forest, oak and oak-pine forest, sometimes in disturbed habitats, secondary forest, slopes, coffee plantations, 800-2200 (3000) m in elevation (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="576859D3EA4075F380F3BA7C739050D9" captionStart="Figure 39" captionStartId="F39" captionText="Figure 39. Map of geographic distribution of L. geminiflora based on herbarium specimen data." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.168.51904.figure39" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/480051" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">39</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="38ED402CDA6B6647552147E2486EA3BF" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.168.51904.figure39" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/480051" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 39" startId="F39">
